rComments: This professor has a world of knowledge and experience to offer; he is incredibly interesting to speak to and is very "chill" as a professor. He will only put in effort to help you if you show genuine interest. He is one of the more mature profs at UofT.

Cool guy. Lectures are to-the-point and straightforward. Vague prompts for assignments, unclear expectations when it comes to marking them (or maybe that was because of a disparity between how the TAs marked them and how he designed the assignments. I'll blame it on the TAs). All in all pretty chill course.
